cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the problem of identifying inaccurate news headlines, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. The use of sequential rules to exploit structure information suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The feature extraction and co-training methods used in the paper are also relevant to Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-categories.
